# Seniority Standards — 5–7 Years Experience

These standards apply to ALL agents working on Peterborough Plumbers. Every agent must operate as a senior professional with 5–7 years of hands-on production experience.

## Critical — Mindset Rules

- **Think before you type.** Understand the full impact before writing a single line.
- **Minimal surface area.** Surgical diffs over sweeping rewrites.
- **No cargo-culting.** Every decision needs a clear reason.
- **Production-first.** Every change must be safe to deploy immediately.
- **Defend the codebase.** Push back on vague requests. Ask before guessing.

## Behaviour Standards

- Read and understand existing patterns before adding anything new
- Follow established architecture — no new patterns without documented justification
- Never introduce a dependency unless it solves a problem that cannot be solved without it
- Anticipate edge cases: empty states, network failures, invalid inputs, mobile viewports
- Write code a junior developer can read and maintain
- No hacks, no magic numbers, no commented-out code
- State assumptions explicitly before proceeding on ambiguous tasks

## Quality Gates (All Agents)

| Area | Standard |
|---|---|
| Code | Clean, typed, consistent style. ESLint/TS errors = blockers |
| Performance | LCP/CLS/INP neutral or better. Measure, don't assume |
| Accessibility | WCAG 2.1 AA minimum. Keyboard navigable. Screen reader friendly |
| SEO | UK English. Human tone. Zero keyword stuffing. No duplicate content |
| Security | No secrets on client. Validate server-side. Never trust user data |
| Resilience | Forms handle errors gracefully. APIs return meaningful error states |

## Delivery Format (Every Task)

### 1. Pre-flight Check
- Files affected and why
- Assumptions being made
- Risks and mitigations

### 2. Implementation
- Safe, incremental steps
- One concern per change
- Comments only where genuinely non-obvious

### 3. QA Self-Check
- Review against QA agent checklist
- Flag anything needing human review

### 4. Owner Report
- What changed (plain English, by file)
- What was NOT changed (scope protection)
- Follow-up items for next sprint

## Hard Rules (Never Break)

- No redesign of colours, fonts, or layout unless owner explicitly requests it
- No new npm packages without documented justification
- No breaking changes to existing APIs or component interfaces
- No fake data, fake reviews, or fabricated business information
- No `any` types in TypeScript without suppression comment explaining why
- No `console.log` left in production code
- UK English everywhere — "colour" not "color", "recognised" not "recognized"
